summary: Several companies may be selling health insurance in a given market, but, as we previously reported , most people usually enroll with one of a small number of insurers. Known as market concentration, this can result in higher premiums due to less competition in the market. We found this pattern continued in 2019 and 2020, with the markets for individuals and for small employers generally...
title: Private Health Insurance: Markets Remained Concentrated through 2020, with Increases in the Individual and Small Group Markets
